- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fixpoint equations and their approximation using abstract interpretation, which are topics closely related to logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses verification tasks such as model-checking, which is a common topic in programming languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper mentions coinductive behavioural equivalences, which are related to automata theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the development of on-the-fly algorithms for characterising the solution of equation systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with verification tasks, which are important in software engineering.
